HEADWORD: Paspy
<hw>Pas"py</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>passe-pied</ets>.]</ety> <def>A kind of minuet, in triple time, of
French origin, popular in the reign of Queen Elizabeth and for some time
after; -- called also <altname>passing measure</altname>, and
<altname>passymeasure</altname>.</def> <rj><au>Percy
Smith.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pasque</ent>⟦br⟧
